  "title": "NEW! Junior Revenue Controller (Law firm)",
  "description": "<ul><li>Assist with the preparation and processing of client invoices, ensuring accuracy and compliance with agreed requirements.</li><li>Support billing and collections activities, including monitoring outstanding invoices and aged balances.</li><li>Maintain and update client and matter financial information within finance systems.</li><li>Prepare standard reports relating to billing, collections, and work in progress.</li><li>Provide financial information and documentation to support internal stakeholders when required.</li><li>Assist with matter and client setup, ensuring billing and rate information is correctly recorded.</li><li>Respond to routine billing and finance-related enquiries from internal teams and clients.</li><li>Support basic credit control activities, including follow-ups on unpaid invoices.</li><li>Assist with month-end and year-end finance processes, including audit support where required.</li><li>Liaise with finance colleagues across teams to resolve billing or system-related queries.</li><li>Support process improvements and help maintain clear and efficient billing procedures.</li></ul><p></p><p>Requirements</p><ul><li>At least 1-2 years of experience in billing </li><li>Proficient in excel functions</li></ul><p><br />Interested applicants please send your resume in MS Word format and attention it to Rachel Yeo (R22104385).<br />Shortlisted candidates will be notified<br />Data provided is for recruitment purposes only<br />www.ambition.com.sg<br />EA Registration Number: R22104385<br />Business Registration Number: 200611680D. License Number: 10C5117</p><p></p>",
